# AI Documentation

## Reference These Files

When making implementation decisions, read and use:

- **ai/SOUL.md** - Architecture, commands, conventions, and patterns. Use for implementation guidance.
- **ai/FEATURES.md** - Current feature list. Use to understand existing capabilities and avoid duplicating features.

## Update FEATURES.md

When implementing **new features** or **significant updates** that add user-facing functionality:

1. Add the feature to [ai/FEATURES.md](ai/FEATURES.md) under the appropriate section (or create a new section).
2. Keep the format consistent: `- Brief description of the feature`
3. Place under the most relevant category (Platform, Real-time, Social, Tabs, Expenses, Invites, etc.).

Do not add minor bug fixes, refactors, or internal changes to FEATURES.md.
